assetProfile.longBusinessSummary: Iwasaki Electric Co., Ltd. manufactures and sells lighting products and industrial systems in Japan, rest of Asia, North America, and internationally. It operates in two segments, Lighting, and Applied Optics and Environment. The company provides street and urbanscape, sports and floodlighting, and commercial and industrial lighting products; lighting control systems; and light source products, such as LED, ceramic metal halide, metal halide, and high-pressure sodium lamps. It also offers applied optics and environmental products, including environmental simulation systems comprising high speed capture lighting products, solar simulation systems, and solar simulation photovoltaic products; UV/EB sterilization systems; water treatment systems; curing/cross-linking/polymerization systems; UV/EB cleaning systems; and light sources for special purposes. The company was formerly known as Iwasaki Radio Engineering and changed its name to Iwasaki Electric Co., Ltd. in 1945. Iwasaki Electric Co., Ltd. was incorporated in 1944 and is headquartered in Tokyo, Japan.
